posts.body: Other than tripfagging, the update worked like a peach
Wait, can you see my posts?

>>dd6d51e6-a549-4479-85e5-86a29f38c5e1
Great. Update worked like a cinch

>>8f28b3e8-ad08-4de1-bf33-4b20e53f5160
>what's the procedure for when it goes wrong?
Death?

Not sure why threads are taking longer to load. Older 08chan was faster in this regard.
Maybe returning to a much simpler script is better. I've seen a few ''anons'' mention that Javascript is quite (((leaky))) and able to force clearnet connections discretely, plus it adds unnecessary processing overhead to simple webpage browsing. I'm assuming a similar setup in HTML and PHP works better for this reason?
Would also be nice to have a larger semblance of anonymity with IDs refreshing automatically after a while. Maybe letting IDs be assigned here instead of ZeroID and only functional for a few posts/hours just like clearnet fullchan?

Outside of these few things, I agree with >>833c3fc5-5ee2-4af1-8ed5-69604d800874. I much prefer the setup here compared to before. Very comfy. Just need a smidge more activity and I can finally ditch the other bunkers.
I'm not sure. I know that posts eventually fall of the catalog, but there's no archival system whatsoever. If I was to guess, I'd say no though, based on how the content.json file works for posts.

This bunker will be slow for now, but hopefully Acid and the /tech/ anons stick around to add performance and QoL updates for when the bunker is needed permanently. ZeroTalk is currently supplying enough decent convo for me personally, and 08chan had similar effortposts shortly after fullchan shut down and before the spamfag took the zite hostage.

>>63abc080-8968-4ce6-b007-99a5fdceb6b0
>People generally have the habit of only believing things from "trustworthy" sources.
That's got everything to do with their laziness. They'll happily swallow any lies they can as long as they get the basic gratifications they desire. Challenge the status quo without and they'll consider it an attack on their way of life, no matter how harmful that system is to them.

ZeroNet can be nothing other than a stop gap to a greater platform seeing as it's under the control of one autistic retard, who if anything happened to him, development would come to a screeching halt.
I personally think decentralization is the way to go, as it's benefits far outweigh it's negatives compared to the clearnet.
